 of them were available on the site, which is about the same or better than some of our top picks. ","Another upside to the site’s small catalog is that all its titles are Digital Rights Management Free. Digital Rights Management, or DRM, prevents users from sharing audio book files, but if you download a book from Audiobookstore.com, you can listen to it on any device you’d like.","You can listen to your library on the web, and the store offers recommendations for your next book. However, you can’t purchase new books from the app, which is a letdown if you finish listening to one on the go.","In the app, the Current Audio Book tab has some narration control options, such as a sleep timer and variable playback speed, and you can find them by clicking on the Settings button. These tools were easier to find in Audiobookstore.com’s app than those for a lot of other services I tested. However, the app isn’t as customizable as others, which may be a problem if you have specific audio book listening habits.","Audiobookstore.com has a FAQs page with a search bar, which is a useful feature when you’re trying to quickly find answers to your questions. The FAQs page was very similar to those on many of the other sites I reviewed, but it would be better if it had more substantial information, especially since the site doesn’t offer phone or live chat support. The service’s email support was reliable, but it’d be nice to get instant help."]},"id":"fcf3e643-f5b8-46df-90c5-a6004e9da355","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"42f8e7f2-1208-4a32-baec-9d199554c2ed","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["For me, a discount-based membership isn’t the best option because it takes me more time to decide on my next book if I’m comparing prices on the titles that I want. Audiobook memberships like AudiobooksNow.com or Audiobookstore.com, on average, cost more per month than credit-based systems. That said, Audiobookstore.com’s downloads are DRM-free, so if you plan on playing books on many different devices, its library might be a good choice."]},"id":"eef791da-dc32-48ec-a808-84d5898feb4e","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_59496","url":"/audiobookstore-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"jessica-richards","url":"/author/jessica-richards","dateCreated":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","name":"Jessica Richards","dateModified":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","id":"nAoS5iTvT5f6rLahJWrxtf","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2014-05-12T17:08:52Z","datePublished":"2014-05-12T17:08:52Z","name":"AudiobookStore","synopsis":"Audiobookstore.com is a discount-based membership plan, much like AudiobooksNow.com. When you enroll, you pay $5.95 for your first audiobook. After that, the $5.95 monthly fee gives you access to discount prices.","review":{"rating":62,"verdict":"While there is a certain allure to being able to share audio book files with family members, Audiobookstore.com&#8217;s discount-based membership program isn&#8217;t the best value out there.","pros":["The titles on Audiobookstore.com are easy to share because they don&#8217;t have Digital Rights Management Protection."],"cons":["The library only has 65,000 titles."]},"strapline":"Audiobookstore.com is a discount-based membership plan, much like AudiobooksNow.com. When you enroll, you pay $5.95 for your first audiobook. After that, the $5.95 monthly fee gives you access to discount prices.","language":"en","dateModified":"2017-09-26T00:00:00Z","id":"NiXXyfKNqV6HW8TkwZAckk","meta":{"title":"AudiobookStore Review - Pros, Cons and Verdict","description":"Audiobookstore.com offers discounts on audio books for a monthly fee. Find out if it is right for you in our review."},"products":[{"slug":"audiobookstore","url":"/product/audiobookstore","dateCreated":"2019-04-16T18:44:22Z","name":"AudiobookStore","dateModified":"2019-04-16T18:44:22Z","id":"qDX9ZjEu6iAxYMLEajcLyj","dateImported":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","site":"to